Job Title:     Principal Research Analyst
Job Location:  PA: Berwyn
Pay Rate:      62-80k
Job Length:    full time
Start Date:    2007-08-22

Company Name:  Vertex, Inc.
Contact:       Dan Burkart
Phone:         484-595-5817
Fax:           610-251-1606

Description:   Position Summary:

A research analyst/principal represents Vertex, internally and externally, as a tax subject matter expert by being knowledgeable of the tax compliance and administration requirements of commercial business entities. The primary tax knowledge indicators include the ability to understand and interpret the application of the tax body of knowledge to general business requirements as represented in Vertex software products. An additional requirement is to represent the tax body of knowledge in Vertex services initiatives and engagements.

Duties and Responsibilities:
These duties include, but are not limited to, the following:  (other duties may be assigned)

1.Research segments of tax law and impose logical structure consistent with Technology platforms and electronically delivered applications
2.Superior ability to communicate verbally and in written form
3.Ability to interface with customers; understand their tax systems and processes; develop solutions to solve their issues
4.Understand how software tax compliance tools work
5.Monitor and analyze legislative activities and court decisions utilizing research tools (e.g. CCH, Lexis-Nexis, Internet, etc.)
6.Identify, understand and communicate changes in the tax law that may impact Vertex products and services
7.Develop and analyze test cases for tax compliance represented in software products
8.Perform testing and quality assurance tasks
9.Develop tax logic scenarios as part of specifications for software product releases
10.Upon request dialogue with Vertex customers about their specific tax requirements and prepare solutions
11.Answer tax related questions for other Vertex entities
12.Provide recommendations to product teams regarding tax processes and rules
13.Prepare white papers and/or reports on taxation topics
14.Prepare and present training sessions on tax related topics

Requirements and Qualifications:

•Education and Training: Advanced Degree in taxation, accounting, business, or law

•Experience: Five or more years of sales tax compliance and administration experience, including tax planning, in a multi-state environment with emphasis on research, use of technology, and audit procedures

Specialized Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:

•Proven ability to analyze and synthesize information; this should include the ability to interpret descriptions of software architecture and conceptually relate them to tax concepts.  It is a requirement that this position be able to interface effectively with operatives from Technology and Development entities.
•Excellent verbal and written communication skills including the ability to reduce the tax law to language understandable by a non-tax professional (decomposition of tax rules).  Moreover it is imperative that this person understands and be capable of executing a strategy for effective oral presentations.  The ability to write for publication in technical journals (topical subjects and white papers) and to make effective presentations to the Vertex customer base is critical.
•Strong aptitude for detail  Strong analytical skills including a solid base in the tax research methodology.  This means that it is not sufficient to be able to regurgitate the tax law.  One must be able to identify all of the issues with respect to a tax problem.  Generally this will require a combination of education, training, and experience.
•Excellent organizational skills
•Working knowledge of Lexis-Nexis, CCH, and other online research tools.  This should include the ability to evaluate authority as all authority does not carry the same precedential value
•Computer literate with experience in PC software applications including word processing programs, spreadsheet programs, PowerPoint, and Internet navigation.  The ability to manipulate data base programs is a plus.
•Understanding of tax information and the ability to formulate interpretations and determine how they apply to Vertex products including the ability to develop conclusions and recommendations.
•Good working knowledge of Vertex software products
•Industry specific knowledge desirable (manufacturing, retail, utilities, etc.)
•Understanding of tax accounting in order to anticipate the reporting needs of Vertex customers
•Understanding of system and software development methodologies, including requirements analysis
•Understanding of computer operating systems (i.e. high level idea of how computers work)
•Understanding process principles and methodologies

Cultural Requirements:

All Vertex employees are expected to:

•Contribute to customer satisfaction by consistently meeting and/or exceeding expectations and commitments to both internal and external customers; by solving customer problems quickly and effectively; and by seeking ways to improve the value of Vertex products and services.
•Contribute to a highly productive work environment by striving for excellence through exceeding expectations; following and/or improving upon established work procedures and methodology; responding to information flow in a timely manner; participating on teams; and acting on performance improvement opportunities where available.
•Foster effective communication and work relationships by practicing active listening skills in order to first understand others; by continually improving own skills in oral and written communications in order to better understand those with whom you work.
•Embrace continuous improvement by proposing new and/or better ways of doing things; supporting the creative and innovative ideas of others; seeking to enhance the core competencies of Vertex wherever possible; and by being receptive and willing to change.
•Promote the fiscal and operational vitality of Vertex by demonstrating an awareness, understanding and fulfillment of the stewardship responsibility which all employees have for the sound use and preservation of the resources, tools and equipment made available to them; and by demonstrating an understanding of, and adherence to, all Vertex Corporate Policies, Procedures and Guidelines.
•Manage time and priorities effectively by completing tasks in a timely manner and meeting personal commitments, managing job-related and personal stress effectively.

